{"kind":"send","message":{"method":"item/completed","params":{"completedAtMs":1781603290757,"item":{"content":[],"id":"rs_015f5abf549e0999016a311bd511d48191babe062291096f7f","summary":["**Crafting safer item access**\n\nI'm thinking about how accessing `items.length` can throw an error if `items` is null or undefined. My idea is that while `!items?.length` does manage nullish values, it unintentionally conflates empty arrays with missing items. I want to make sure I handle both cases without mixing them up. So, I'll explore crafting a more robust solution that clearly differentiates between an empty array and an undefined `items`."],"type":"reasoning"},"threadId":"019ecfd4-a3f6-7cb1-8e95-ac17ade5a981","turnId":"019ecfd4-a48f-7e22-9161-e99bcc69e937"}}}
